	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f98668092644255>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=3&mid=98668092644255>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=98668092644255>Another note on the combine change</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=98668092644255#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sat, Apr 7th 6:02 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=43653><span id=Scholar>GLASS</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>202 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Hey all.&nbsp;&nbsp;Since this combine change still seems like a pretty hot topic, I'd like to post my latest findings on the subject.  I was fortunate enough to stumble onto a player last night selling tailored small bags and asked about the wt. and capacity.  They hold four items (less than the sewing kits I know, but wait it gets better), weigh 0.4 and have a weight reduction bonus of 10%.  It's nothing exceptional but at 1pp per bag it's a great alternative.  I bought two, one for my Iksar monk and one for my buddy's Human monk.  <br><br>Unfortunately these items seem way tougher to get a hold of in Kunark than other places, so Iksars might have a harder time finding them.  I bought mine with my Ranger and plan on taking down on the boat as soon as possible.<br><br>Hope this helps!<br><br>Zasshatiz - 19 Iksar Monk<br>Gluadilae - 19 Wood Elf Ranger & Master Fletcher<br>Circle of Radiance Guild<br>Luclin Server</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
	     <tr><td colspan=2 align=right class=mform id=fs8>0 Replies</td></tr>
