	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Apr 5th 9:12 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=16689><span id=Scholar>Badger</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>62 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.16]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>How does this formula work for lower levels? At 13th level, it tells me I'm doing negative damage. I hate to think I'm healing these guys when I hit them...<br><br>Garren Ravenclaw <br>Monk of the 13th Season <br>Silent Fist Clan<br>Morelle-Thule &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
	     <tr><td colspan=2 align=right class=mform id=fs8>1 Replies</td></tr>
	     </form></table><tr><td colspan=2><ul><table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f98649574093146>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=3&mid=98649574093146>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=98649574093146>RE: Should I Start Over?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=98649574093146#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Apr 5th 2:35 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=9543><span id=Scholar>Landrion</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>35 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>There is no way in that formula to get a negative result.<br><br>Let me break down the formula to make it simpler and more understandable (hopefully), start with the innermost parenthesis.&nbsp;&nbsp;For the purposes of this explanation we will use Garren as the example with a few made up numbers to fill in what we don't know.<br><br>level=13<br>str=100<br>weaponskill=70 (this is max for 13, as (level*5)+5 gives us)<br>weapondamage=6 (his fists at level 13 are 6dmg/36dly)<br><br>The formula we will use is:<br><br>max=weapondamage*((str+weaponskill)/100)<br><br>(we won't bother with the part after that because you don't even get a 1 until level 28 as that part of it is meant to be a bonus)<br><br>so:<br><br>str+weaponskill<br>100+70 gives us 170<br><br>/100 gives us a player factor of 1.7<br><br>weapondamage *<br>we multiply the weapondamage by our factor<br>6*1.7<br><br>so our max then is 10 (10.2)<br><br>I'll plug all the numbers into the formula so we can see it:<br><br>max=weapondamage * ((str+weaponskill)/100)<br><br>so...<br><br>10.2=6 * ((100+70)/100)<br><br>So now this is clear as crystal or more like mud.  I hope the former is true.<br><br>Zzaarno Painmaker<br>Monk of the 22nd Season<br>Court of Pain<br>Tholuxe-Paells</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
