	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=3&mid=98597527973683>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=98597527973683>RE: Where do i put my monk skill points at level up?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=98597527973683#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Mar 30th 1:01 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=4986><span id=Scholar>Alerithon</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>92 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.23]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I think the common view is to save your points for things you really need, and that either don't see much everyday use, or are expensive or time consuming to practice.&nbsp;&nbsp;As a monk, you already are an uber martial artist...doing what you naturally do (fight) will soon max out all your combat skills.  By level 10, unless you are doing some serious power leveling, your hth and other combat skills should be maxed (combat skill increase does require a challenge, so you should not see many, if any, skill ups from fighting greens...skills like intimidate and disarm are exceptions).  <br><br>Mend is a good investment, as the lower your skill, the greater the chance for it to fail.  But you will want to save some points for when you get feign death at 17.  This skill is the monk's greatest tool and weapon.  It is what makes you a valued member of a group, and will save your life (and the lives of your party) time and time again.<br><br>After, you may consider saving skill points for the new special combats...as these start relatively low compared to your other combat skills, giving dragon punch and flying kick a boost can help maintain your fightin effectiveness.<br><br>I play on E'Ci, and am nearing mastery of tailoring.  I recently sold a full set of cured silk for 100 plat.  I generally charge 1-2 plat per ac point.</p>&nbsp;<br>Alerithon Tigerspirit<br>29 rank monk, E'Ci<br>Avatara</td></td></tr>
