	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=16689><span id=Scholar>Badger</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>62 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.08]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Well, I just got to 12th, so here's my experience on Skill points:<br><br>I spent only one point on HTH, Dual Wield & Dodge and have no problems maxing them out at each level.<br>I picked up Block this level, it's almost maxed already.<br>Minor skills like Swim, Safe Fall and Sneak are very easy to work on in downtime (waiting for the boat, camping a spawn...)<br>The special attacks are a little slower to increase, but I get a new one every few level so I don't waste points beyond the one to start it.<br>The skills I dump most of the points in are (in order):<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;Mend: This WILL save your life. It can never have to many points.<br>  Bind Wounds: For the 6 minutes the Mend recycles<br>  Tailoring: For Cured Silk and bandages (for the Bind Wound)<br><br>Once I get to 17th, Feign Death will take the majority of the points, but that's in the future...<br><br>Garren Ravenclaw <br>Monk of the 12th Season <br>Silent Fist Clan<br>Morelle-Thule <br></p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
