	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Mar 29th 9:35 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=39551><span id=Guru>Osano</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>171 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.66]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I think it's going to be difficult to find a consensus on best place for skill points, as so much of what you skill up in quickly has to do with playing style.<br><br>For instance, those who group with healers a lot probably will want to put points in Mend, as you won't use it as much.&nbsp;&nbsp;I solo most of the time, on the other hand, and have kept mend level-capped with no problems.  I'm sure you can think of similar situations with most of the other skills.  Put points in whatever you just can't seem to use enough.  Safefall was always my personal nemesis.  Now, Instill Doubt is my laggard.<br><br>On your second point, I'm nearly certain, just based on my own experience, that you have a better chance for combat skill increases fighting tougher monsters.  I very rarely get an increase fighting greens, and get them quite quickly against tough blues.<br><br>Finally, I've seen a pretty wide range of opinions on the proper price for cured silk, but 2-3PP/AC seems to be about the consensus.  I'm currently at 56 on tailoring, and am wearing all cured silk that I've made (excepting Woven Goves, Spiked Collar, Monk Sash and Headband). Once my fail rate is to the point where I can make a set without going through 4 stacks of swatches, I plan on selling it for 2PP/AC.  This seems, from the Tailor's standpoint, to be a reasonable balance between profit and ability to move the stuff, at least on Tholuxe-Paells.<br><br>Good Luck.<br><br>Osano -- sloooooooooowly getting tailoring up to backpack levels.<br><br>P.S.  Looks like Glass and I posted at the exact same time.  At least the info is consistent!</p>&nbsp;<br>Osano<br>Level 44 Human Monk<br>Tholuxe-Paells</td></td></tr>
