	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Mar 30th 12:53 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=43455><span id= >Kameni</span></a><br><span id=notbold>8 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Hehe, ask the same question, get 20 different answers.&nbsp;&nbsp;My vote is pop 1 point into each new skill as you get it and save the rest till you get Feign Death and/or Instill Doubt.  Since you can't count on Mend until you have about 80 skill in it, keep your mend key depressed all the time until then.  Use it whether you have hp to heal or not. Once you get Feign Death, pop as many skill points as you can into it, then when hunting, mention it to your group that you are going to practise Feign Death if you happen to have the opportunity (ie you're not pulling mobs for them).  Instill Doubt, do the same thing.  Somone previously mentioned here for ID a special hotkey that you can set up to max it as quickly as possible.  Go into your socials and type the following:<br><br>/doability #x (this is your Instill Doubt)<br>/pause 37<br>/doability #y (this is your special attack)<br><br>This helps you time your ID perfectly so that you don't have your special attack interrupting your ID.  Hope this helps.<br><br><br>Kameni<br>Monk of the 30th season, Vallon Zek</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
