	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=39551><span id=Guru>Osano</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>171 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I can't speak for the higher levels, but I think it's quite easy to solo with a monk at least into the 20s.<br><br>Once you get Feign Death at 17, grind it out and level cap it as fast as you can.<br><br>Then, you can pull singles out of camps all by yourself, and if you get into a bad spot, just feign and rest a bit while the baddies wander away.<br><br>As for 1HB, I just take my old trusty Staff out of the bank to level cap the skill each time I level then it goes right back in.&nbsp;&nbsp;With the hand-to-hand ability (went and fought for a bit near the entrance to U Guk until I got my mesh gloves), I just don't see a reason to worry about 1HB too much until you can get yourself one of the really good higher level weapons.  Just keep the skill up.<br><br>Osano, 20th level monk</p>&nbsp;<br>Osano<br>Level 44 Human Monk<br>Tholuxe-Paells</td></td></tr>
